&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772622012391263701357_0_10332616ff4cd8a32372b3e1a8a161ce.jpg?&amp;amp;h=a17cc485faeb5fa692d05518c4362942&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Whether in its natural wonders, cherished traditions, or cultural quirks, the many aspects that blend together to form the United States&#39; dynamic character are as varied as the country itself. With the U.S. celebrating its 250th birthday on July 4, National Geographic looks out across the most distinctive and superlative places and experiences that define the country across 50 states and five major territories.&lt;br&gt;Discover the wonders of America at the link in bio.&lt;br&gt;Photographs by Brian Stevens; Mark Thiessen (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/thiessenphoto/&quot;&gt;@thiessenphoto&lt;/a&gt; ); milehightraveler, Getty Images; George Grall, National Geographic Image Collection; Jeff Minton and Chris McPherson; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/carolineallison3356/&quot;&gt;@carolineallison3356&lt;/a&gt; .</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772622012391263701357/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772622012391263701357</guid><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 12:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>This shot was taken in Whiteness Voe on the Shetland Islands, Scotland. It is a solar-powered sea slug (Elysia viridis). I encountered it on a shallow...</title><description>&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772152044586816233171_0_8be77ee84f5086da23e404aa541f9fa0.jpg?&amp;amp;h=b75fd61c5c28d0eaaea9d8433d9863bd&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;This shot was taken in Whiteness Voe on the Shetland Islands, Scotland. It is a solar-powered sea slug (Elysia viridis). I encountered it on a shallow dive and was amazed to see it fully unfurled, revealing its leaf-like form and the stunning galaxy-like pattern on its back. Amazing to think a sea slug evolved the same shape as a leaf to harness the power of the sun!&lt;br&gt;This photo by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/lona_brak/&quot;&gt;@lona_brak&lt;/a&gt;  is from our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/natgeoyourshot/&quot;&gt;@natgeoyourshot&lt;/a&gt;  community.</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772152044586816233171/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772152044586816233171</guid><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>They&#39;re graceful, pink, and very social—until another bird steps a little too close for comfort. 😅 Do you share @joelsartore &#39;s love for flamingos...</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772152152444763722058_0_a0f93e5d535359d2339740b41cb4c2a8.jpg?&amp;amp;h=4c01b9f89c3b73e1945f766b72c14ea3&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;They&#39;re graceful, pink, and very social—until another bird steps a little too close for comfort. 😅 Do you share &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/joelsartore/&quot;&gt;@joelsartore&lt;/a&gt; &#39;s love for flamingos?&lt;br&gt;We’re celebrating 20 years of the National Geographic #PhotoArk, an audacious project documenting the world&#39;s incredible biodiversity and highlighting the importance of conservation through photography. Check out more of Joel’s work in his &quot;Photo Ark: Animals of Earth&quot; exhibition at the National Geographic Museum of Exploration, opening June 26th.</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772152152444763722058/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772152152444763722058</guid><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Nat Geo Explorer @andresruzo and ABC News&#39; @jujuchangabc came across these plumeria flowers left as an offering near Rainbow Falls in Hawaii while sea...</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772495853186173732836_0_0c608354fe93057050897007281a3da4.jpg?&amp;amp;h=ff1c4479852c6918d57fe1d8c8ca4d97&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Nat Geo Explorer &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/andresruzo/&quot;&gt;@andresruzo&lt;/a&gt;  and ABC News&#39; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/jujuchangabc/&quot;&gt;@jujuchangabc&lt;/a&gt;  came across these plumeria flowers left as an offering near Rainbow Falls in Hawaii while searching for the Seven Natural Wonders of America. A sacred site in Hawaiian mythology, Rainbow Falls is the legendary home of Hina, the Hawaiian moon goddess and mother of the demigod Māui.&lt;br&gt;Discover more beauty and nature in the final Wonders of America list, revealed during the 24-hour “Disney Celebrates America” live event special on July 4th.</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772495853186173732836/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772495853186173732836</guid><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Inside a vast subterranean network of tunnels and underground highways, the behavior of mole-rats has caught the attention of scientists. The rodents ...</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772135147241638727129_0_9d4d86a76f6fc47d323b63750aefa75b.jpg?&amp;amp;h=8cb0d582efdbc8b0e0c905663ef6fee9&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Inside a vast subterranean network of tunnels and underground highways, the behavior of mole-rats has caught the attention of scientists. The rodents tend to a food source in a way that could be compared to farming, with some researchers suggesting mole-rats may have been the first mammals to farm in Africa—or anywhere else.&lt;br&gt;Hear what experts have to say at the link in bio.&lt;br&gt;Video by Lion Mountain Media</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772135147241638727129/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772135147241638727129</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Deep beneath the waves off Costa Rica&#39;s coast, scientists not only discovered a new species of octopus but also a nursery where over 100 Dorado octopu...</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772386716533413142958_0_af34f18a52af9424540f45fe04476c15.jpg?&amp;amp;h=14534dd08a05a5c813b8fdedf0050241&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Deep beneath the waves off Costa Rica&#39;s coast, scientists not only discovered a new species of octopus but also a nursery where over 100 Dorado octopuses tend their eggs near hydrothermal vents. 🐙&lt;br&gt;#SecretsOfTheOctopus is streaming on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/disneyplus/&quot;&gt;@DisneyPlus&lt;/a&gt;  and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/hulu/&quot;&gt;@hulu&lt;/a&gt; .</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772386716533413142958/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772386716533413142958</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Captured by photographer Jason Siegel @jsiegelphotography , eagle hunter Rinat Mirlanov rests with his golden eagle above the village of Bokonbayevo i...</title><description>&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772135726131445102838_0_4e4aa10b03ac63c08b865e48ed86a5ec.jpg?&amp;amp;h=7545e04e34794f1952b9a7bdf5ddacc8&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Captured by photographer Jason Siegel &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/jsiegelphotography/&quot;&gt;@jsiegelphotography&lt;/a&gt; , eagle hunter Rinat Mirlanov rests with his golden eagle above the village of Bokonbayevo in Kyrgyzstan. Eagle hunting, known as berkutchi in Kyrgyz, is an ancient tradition in the country in which hunters train golden eagles to hunt small prey like foxes and hares, requiring years of trust and reliance between the eagle and the hunter. Although eagle hunting today is considered more of a hobby, it was originally used as a means of survival, providing villagers with both food and clothing.&lt;br&gt;See more Photos of the Day at the link in bio.</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772135726131445102838/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772135726131445102838</guid><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>The platypus is one of only two mammals that lay eggs. That&#39;s just the start of what makes these unusual creatures so fascinating—and why they once b...</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772135154344273242456_0_383e07235ba171b30e00e77fa996c695.jpg?&amp;amp;h=a37e7c4d110c961c5e5babe2966303e8&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;The platypus is one of only two mammals that lay eggs. That&#39;s just the start of what makes these unusual creatures so fascinating—and why they once baffled scientists.</description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772135154344273242456/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772135154344273242456</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Can’t decide if these Tibetan fox cubs are at their most adorable when they have energy to burn or when they’re all tuckered out.</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6772504751466657285747_0_a46ab2d88d08bb6870fd7bd40ebc53c8.jpg?&amp;amp;h=72bbfa87bb64eec6019f534220e72c4a&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Can’t decide if these Tibetan fox cubs are at their most adorable when they have energy to burn or when they’re all tuckered out.&lt;br&gt;#TheHiddenKingdomsOfChina is now streaming on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/disneyplus/&quot;&gt;@DisneyPlus&lt;/a&gt; </description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6772504751466657285747/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6772504751466657285747</guid><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>@antoni is on a quest to find the best sights, tastes, and experiences the world has to offer, and you&#39;re invited.</title><description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://sp1.picnob.com/p/pt_6727176351402334302649_0_10fdcc95a86a023f5ac87cc064bd6c26.jpg?&amp;amp;h=ce23d87e3b256eb2008d94fd6180619a&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;no-referrer&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/antoni/&quot;&gt;@antoni&lt;/a&gt;  is on a quest to find the best sights, tastes, and experiences the world has to offer, and you&#39;re invited.&lt;br&gt;#BestOfTheWorld with Antoni Porowski premieres Sunday, June 7 at 9/8c on National Geographic. Stream on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/disneyplus/&quot;&gt;@DisneyPlus&lt;/a&gt;  and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.picnob.com/profile/hulu/&quot;&gt;@hulu&lt;/a&gt; </description><link>https://www.picnob.com/post/6727176351402334302649/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">6727176351402334302649</guid><pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 07:12:23 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>